obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (39549)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39549&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Murshidabad Estate`
  line `Administration Act, 1933.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) It extends to whole of India except ^2`
  line `[the territories which, immediately before the 1st November`
  line `1956, were comprised in Part B States].]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for “Part B States”.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (39550)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39550&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or`
  line context,--
  line
  line `(1) "Immoveable properties of the estate" means the properties contained in the`
  line `Schedules of immoveable property annexed to the Indenture included in and confirmed`
  line `by the Murshidabad Act, 1891 (15 of 1891), with any additional immoveable property`
  line `added thereto under sub-section (1) of section 3 of that Act, and includes all immoveable`
  line `property acquired under the provisions of section 32 of the Land Acquisition Act, 1894`
  line `(1 of 1894);`
  line
  line `(2) "issues and profits of the immoveable properties of the estate" includes all money`
  line `awarded under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), as compensation for the`
  line `acquisition of any of the immoveable properties of the estate together with interest thereon;`
  line
  line `(3) "Manager" means the officer appointed under section 3;`
  line
  line `(4) "Nawab Bahadur" means the Nawab Bahadur of Murshidabad for the time`
  line being;
  line
  line `^1* * * * *;`
  line
  line `(6) "Board of Revenue" means the Board of Revenue, ^2[West Bengal];`
  line
  line `(7) "Prescribed" means provided for by this Act or by rules made under section 28.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Clause (5) omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Bengal".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (39551)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of Manager.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39551&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^2[The State Government of ^1[West Bengal] (hereafter in`
  line `this Act referred to as "the State Government")] may, at any time after ^3`
  line `[the State`
  line `Government] has entered upon the immovable properties of the estate in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Murshidabad Act, 1891 (15 of 1891), by an order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette appoint an officer for the management on behalf of ^3[the State Government] of the`
  line `whole or any portion of these properties and of the rents, issues and profits thereof and for`
  line `the reception and application of the monthly sum of Rs. 19,166 -10-8 payable from the`
  line `Government Treasury at Berhampore in the district of Murshidabad in West Bengal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the management shall cease from such date ^4[as may, having regard to the`
  line `circumstances or in the event of the death of a Nawab Bahadur, be notified] by the State`
  line `Government in the Official Gazette as the date of withdrawal by ^5[the State Government] from entry`
  line `upon the immovable properties of the estate.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Bengal".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for the "The L. G.".`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "the Secretary of State".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by West Ben. Act 20 of 1959, s. 2, for "as may be notified".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Secretary of State".`
  line
  line `6. The Second proviso omitted by West Ban. Act 20 of 1959, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (39552)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Effect of order under section 3.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39552&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On the publication of an order for the appointment`
  line `of a Manager under section 3, the following consequences shall ensure:—`
  line
  line `first, all proceedings which may then be pending in any Civil Court in respect of any`
  line `debts or liabilities to which the Nawab Bahadur may be subject shall be barred, and all`
  line `processes, executions and attachments for or in respect of such debts and liabilities shall`
  line `become null and void;`
  line
  line `secondly, so long as such management continues, no suit or proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the Nawab Bahadur, ^1*** ^2`
  line `[or the State of ^3`
  line `[West Bengal]] or the Manager, in respect of any`
  line `any debt or liability to which the Nawab Bahadur is subject, nor shall the Nawab Bahadur be`
  line `liable to arrest for or in respect of the debts and liabilities to which he was at the time of`
  line `such publication subject or in execution of any decree obtained before such publication nor`
  line `shall his moveable property be liable to attachment or sale, unde r process of any Court for`
  line `or in respect of such debts and liabilities;`
  line
  line `thirdly, so long as such management continues—`
  line
  line `(a) the Nawab Bahadur shall be incompetent to mortgage, charge, lease,`
  line `settle or alienate the immoveable properties of the estate, or to grant valid`
  line `receipts for the rents and profits arising or accruing therefrom;`
  line
  line `(b) such property shall be exempt from attachment or sale unde r process of`
  line `any Court; and`
  line
  line `(c) the Nawab Bahadur shall be incapable of entering into any contract which may`
  line `involve him in pecuniary liability; and`
  line
  line `fourthly, any amount awarded, before the entry ^4`
  line `[of the State Government] upon the`
  line `immovable properties of the estate, under the Land Acquisition Act, 1894 (1 of 1894), by`
  line `way of compensation for immoveable properties of the estate acquired under that Act, if`
  line `the amount has been invested in securities under section 32 of that Act or is deposited in`
  line `Court pending such investment in land or securities, shall, together with all interest and`
  line `other proceeds thereof not already paid to any person under the provisions of any law, be`
  line `deliverable to the Manager on behalf ^4`
  line `[of the State Government] to be disposed of in such`
  line `manner as the ^5`
  line `[State Government] may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or the Secretary of State" omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Bengal".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "of the Secretary of State".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Secretary of State".`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (39553)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Suits and appeals during management.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39553&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `So long as the appointment of the Manager`
  line continues—
  line
  line `(1) in every suit or appeal to which ^2*** ^3`
  line `[* * * the State of ^1`
  line `[West Bengal] in`
  line `possession is a party the Manager shall be named as ^4[its representative] for the purpose of such suit`
  line `or appeal;`
  line
  line `(2) in every pending suit or appeal concerning the properties under management ^5`
  line `[the State of`
  line ^6
  line `[West Bengal]] in possession shall be a party in place of the Nawab Bahadur and the Manager shall`
  line `be named as the representative of ^5`
  line `[the State of ^6`
  line `[West Bengal]] in possession for the purpose of the`
  line `suit or appeal; and no application in any sucn suit or appeal shall be made to the Court on behalf of`
  line ^5
  line `[the State of ^6`
  line `[West Bengal]] in possession except by the Manager;`
  line
  line `(3) the Court upon application by the Manager or by any party to the suit may order that the plaint or`
  line `memorandum of appeal be amended so as to conform with the requirements of clause (1) or that the`
  line `Manager be named as the representative of the ^7`
  line `[State of West Bengal] in possession as required by clause`
  line `clause (2) of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Bengal".`
  line
  line `2. The words "the Secretary of State or" omitted, ibid., s.9.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "his representative".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Secretary of State".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Bengal".`
  line
  line `7. Subs., ibid., for "Secretary of State".`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (39554)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Manager to receive rents, issues and profits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "Bengal".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39554&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Manager shall receive and recover all`
  line `rents, issues and profits due in respect of the immoveable properties of the estate, and shall upon`
  line `receiving such rents, issues and profits give receipts therefor.`
  line
  line `(2) The Manager shall receive the monthly sum of Rs. 19,166-10-8 payable from the Government`
  line `Treasury at Berhampore in the district of Murshidabad in ^1`
  line `[West Bengal] and shall give receipts therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (39555)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Application by Manager of sums received.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39555&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) From the sums received under sub-sections (1) and`
  line
  line `(2) of section 6, the Manager shall pay—`
  line
  line `first, to the Nawab Bahadur such monthly sum, not being in any case less than Rs. 9, 583-5-4, as the`
  line `State Government may fix in this behalf;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[secondly, the allowances, if any, payable under section 3 of the Murshidabad Act, 1946];`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[thirdly], the Government revenue, cesses, rates and taxes and all debts and liabilities for the time`
  line `being due or incurred to Government or to any local authority;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[fourthly], in the case of property held by the Nawab Bahadur as tenant, the rent and cess due`
  line `to the superior landlord in respect of the said property;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[fifthly], the cost of such repairs and improvements of the immoveable properties`
  line `of the estate as appear necessary to the Manager and are approved by the Board of Revenue,`
  line
  line `and shall apply the residue to the discharge of the costs of the management, to the payment of expenditure`
  line `incurred in litigation and to the settlement in accordance with the scheme approved by the Board of`
  line `Revenue under section 14 of such debts and liabilities of the Nawab Bahadur as may be estsblished under`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the pay out of the sums`
  line `received under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 6 any sum required to meet such expenditure on other`
  line `object or for any other purpose as the ^5`
  line `[State Government] may from time to time sanction.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Bengal Act 15 of 1946, s. 5.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "secondly".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "thirdly".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "fourthly".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Secretary of State".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (39556)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Notice to claimants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39556&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the publication of the order for the appointment of a`
  line `Manager under section 3 the Manager shall publish in the prescribed manner a notice in English and Bengali`
  line `calling upon all persons having claims against the Nawab Bahadur to notify such claims in writing to the`
  line `Manager within six months from the date of the notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (39557)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Presentation of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39557&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every such claimant shall, along with his claim, present to the`
  line `Manager full particulars thereof, together with all documents on which he relies in support thereof, and the`
  line `Manager may refuse to receive in evidence on the claimants behalf at the investigation of the claim any`
  line `document not so presented.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (39558)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Debt not duly notified to be barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39558&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every debt or liability, except debts due or liabilities incurred to the Government or to any local authority and rent due to a superior landlord from the Nawab Bahadur as tenant of any property, which is not duly notified to the Manager within the time and in the manner mentioned in sections 8 and 9 shall be barred:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Manager is satisfied that the claimant was for reasonable cause unable to comply with the provisions of sections 8 and 9, the Manager may admit his claim within a further period of six months from the expiration of the period of six months specified in section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (39559)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Determination of debts.`
  content `The Manager shall in the prescribed manner determine the amount of the principal of all debts and liabilities not barred under section 10 justly due to the several creditors of the Nawab Bahadur and to persons holding mortgages, charges or liens on the property of the Nawab Bahadur, and shall determine in like manner the interest, if any, due at the date of such determination in respect of such debts and liabilities and may reduce the rates of interest charged as appears to him just and proper.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39559&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (39560)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to inquire into consideration for leases, etc.`
  content `The Manager may inquire into the sufficiency of the consideration for which any lease, settlement, grant, mortgage, charge or lien was given and whether it was given in contravention of the conditions of the Murshidabad Act, 1891(15 of 1891), and if satisfied that the consideration was insufficient or that such lease, settlement, grant, mortgage, charge or lien was given in contravention of the said Act may, by order in writing, set a side or modify such lease, settlement, grant, mortgage, charge or lien; and any such order, subject to the appeal provided insection 13, shall have the force of a decree of a competent Civil Court andbe enforceable as such.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39560&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (39561)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Appeals to Board of Revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39561&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1)An appeal shall lie to the Board of Revenue against any order by the Manager—`
  line
  line `(a) refusingto receive a document under section 9; or`
  line
  line `(b) refusing to admit a claim under the proviso to section 10; or`
  line
  line `(c) determining the amount of a debt or liability or of interest thereon, or reducing the rate of interest, under. section 11; or`
  line
  line `(d) setting asideor modifying a lease, settlement, grant, mortgage, charge or lien under section 12.`
  line
  line `(2)If no such appeal is preferred within six weeks from the date of the order, the decision of the Manager shall, subject to the provisions of section 22, be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (39562)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Scheme for settlement of debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39562&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenthe amount due in respect of the debts and liabilities mentioned in section 11 has been finally determined, the Manager shall prepare and submit to the Board of Revenue a schedule of such debts and liabilities, and a scheme for the settlement thereof in whole or in part out of the residue referred to in section 7 annually available during the lifetime of the Nawab Bahadur; and the Board of Revenue may approve the scheme without modification or subject to such modification as it deems expedient.`
  line
  line `(2)The scheme shall provide for payment in full, as soon as may be, of—`
  line
  line `(a) first, arrears of wages due to servants of the Nawab Bahadur, determined in accordance with the forgoing provisions, and`
  line
  line `(b) secondly, claims of each creditor whose claims in the aggregate do not exceed five hundred rupees, as so determined;`
  line
  line `and the scheme shall further provide that any balance left after meeting the above claims and each annual residue thereafter shall be distributed rateably among the other creditors of the Nawab Bahadur inpayment of their claims, as so determined.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (39563)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to call for further particulars.`
  content `The Manager may from time to time call for further and more detailed particulars of any claim preferred before him under this Act and may at his discretion refuse to proceed with the investigation of the claim until such particulars are supplied.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39563&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (39564)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to summon witnesses.`
  content `The Managermay for the purpose of any investigation under this Act summon and enforce the attendance of witnesses and compel them to give evidence, and compel the production of documents, by the same means and as far as possible in the same manner as is provided in the case of a Civil Court by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39564&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (39565)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Investigation to be deemed a judicial proceeding.`
  content `Everyinvestigation conducted by the Manager with reference to any claim preferred before him under this Act, or to any matter connected with such claim, shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860); and everystatement made by any person examined by or before the Manager with reference to any such investigation, whether upon oath or otherwise, shall be deemed to be evidence within the meaning of the said Code.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39565&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (39566)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to order production of accounts, papers, etc., and evidence of title .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39566&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) TheCollector of Murshidabad may on the application of the Manager order all persons who are or were in the employ of the estate of the Nawab Bahadur to attend before him; and may order any person to deliver up any accounts, papers or moveable property belonging to the estate or any accounts or papers relating to the immoveable property of the estate or to any other property of the estate which the Manager has reason to believe are in such persons possession or control; and may order all hodlers of tenures or under-tenures on any such property to produce their titles to such tenures or undertenures.`
  line
  line `(2)Any person who refuses to comply with an order under sub-section (1) may be punished by the Collector of Murshidabad with fine not exceeding five hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal shall lie to the Board of Revenue against any order of fine passed by the Collector under sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (39567)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers of Manager for realisation of rents, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Secretary of State".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39567&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Manager shall have, for thepurpose of realising and recovering the rents, issues and profits of the immoveable properties of the estate, the same powers as the Nawab Bahadur would have had for such purpose had the ^1[State Government] not entered into the said properties, and all arrears of rent and all demands recoverable as rent, and all interest due on such arrears or demands shall together with all costs incurred for realising the same be recoverable as public demands.`
  line
  line `(2)If such properties or any part thereof be in the possession of any mortgagee or conditional vendee, the Manager may apply to the Collector within whose jurisdiction the property is situated, and the Collector shall cause the same to be delivered to the Manager as if a decree therefor had been made in his favour, but without prejudice to the mortgagee or vendee preferring his claim under the provisions elsewhere contained in this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) If such properties or any part thereof be in possession of a Receiverappointed by a Court, the Manager may apply to the Court, and the Court shall cause the same to be delivered to the Manager together with art receipts which may be in the hands of the Receiver or the Court at the time of the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (39568)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39568&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Manager may, subjectto the prescribed conditions, make settlementof all or any of the immoveable properties of the estate and may for this purpose execute any lease or counterpart of a lease:`
  line
  line `Provided that, unless the settlement is of a kind authorised by rule made under section 28, its terms and conditions shall have been previously approved by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (39569)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power of Manager to contract and take action for the benefit of the estate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39569&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Manager may enter into any contract or take any action which in his opinion is necessary for the proper care andmanagement of the immoveable properties of the estate and of the rents, issues and profits thereof or for the maintenance of the position and dignity of the Nawab Bahadur and which is notinconsistent with any provision of this Act or with any rule made under section 28:`
  line
  line `Provided that if he is not empowered by any other provision of this Act or by any rule made under section 28 to enter on such contract or to take such action he shall obtain the previous sanction of the Board of Revenue before entering upon the contract or taking the action.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (39570)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Powers or supervision and control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39570&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Allorders or proceedings of the Manager in the exercise of his functions under this act shall be subject to the supervision and control of the Board of Revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) All orders or proceedings of the Board of Revenue under this Actshall be subject to the supervision and control of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The supervising authority in each case may of its own motion review and if it thinks fit revise, modify or reverse any order of proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (39571)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Manager to be deemed a public servant.`
  content `The Manager shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39571&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (39572)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Recovery of fines.`
  content `Any fine imposed under this Act shall be recoverable as a public demand.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39572&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (39573)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Bar of suits, etc., against certain persons.`
  content `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any person in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39573&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (39574)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power of State Government to make orders.`
  content `If at the time of the withdrawal of the ^1[StateGovernment] from entry upon the immoveable properties of the estate, any difficulty arises in connection with the restoration to the Nawab Bahadur or to his successor of the properties and rights possessed and exercised by the ^1[State Government], the State Government may by order authorise the doing of any matter or thing which appears to it necessary to facilitate such restoration.`
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Secretary of State".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39574&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (39575)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Effect of withdrawal from entry by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "Secretary of State".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39575&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this or any other Act, the withdrawal bythe ^1[State Government] from entry upon the immoveable properties of the estate shall not have the effect of reviving any of the proceeding referred to in clause first of section 4 if the debt or liability in respect of which such proceedings were instituted is barred under section 10.`
  line
  line `Nothing in section 4 shall bar the revival after such withdrawal of any other of the proceedings referred to in the said clause:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Court shall entertain any suit ofproceeding against the Nawab Bahadur in which the amount claimed is in excess of the amount determined under section 11, 13 or 22, as the case may be, together with any further interest due thereon, or in which interest is claimed at a rate higher than the rate determined as just and proper under those sections.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (39576)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774&sectionId=39576&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00065_193323_1523350928774
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of Revenue may, with the previous sancion of the State Government ^1[and by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules] for the purposeof carrying into effect all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Inparticular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the security to be requiredfrom subordinat e officers under Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the Manager in the discharge of his functions under this Act, the accounts which shall be kept by him, and the manner in which such accounts shall be audited;`
  line
  line `(c) the terms, conditions and limitations under which leases may be granted;`
  line
  line `(d) the notices to be given under this Act and the manner of publication of such notices`
  line
  line `(e) theprocedure to the followed by claimants in presenting claims, and by the Manager in the investigation of such claims;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure to be followed in determining under section 11 the debts and liabilities due to creditors and other persons;`
  line
  line `(g) the allowance of interest on the principal of eachof the debts and liabilities as determined under section 11 from the date on which it was incurred to the date of the determination and on the aggregate amount of such debts and liabilities from the date of the determination to the date of payment;`
  line
  line `(h) the preparation of the schedule of debts and liabilities and of the scheme referred to in section 14 and the order of payment of such debts and liabilities;`
  line
  line `(i) the power s of the Ma na ger t o ma ke or s ancti on s ettle ment s; and`
  line
  line `(j) the procedure to the followed in appeals under this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule made by the Board of Revenue under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "make rules"(w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2 Added byAct 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `मुर्शिदाबाद संपदा प्रशासन अधिनियम,1933`
